<span id="v.iii.lxxv-p2"></span><span class="c12"><span
id="v.iii.lxxv-p2.1"></span>Anatolius <span
id="fr_2491"></span>[2492](#fn_2491.md) </span> of Alexandria, bishop of
Laodicea in Syria, who flourished under the emperors Probus and Carus,
was a man of wonderful learning in arithmetic, geometry, astronomy,
grammar, rhetoric, and dialectic. We can get an idea of the greatness of
his genius from the volume which he wrote *On the passover* and his ten
books *On the institutes of arithmetic.*

